main event: A multi-colored, 'X' shaped object was observed moving slowly across the sky for almost 20 minutes in Wadena, Minnesota on January 15, 1957.
interesting points: The object was described as making a 'humming sound'.
The object disappeared to the east.
The sighting was concluded to have characteristics of a balloon observation.
No balloons or planes were reported to be released or flying in the area at the time.
The sighting was investigated by the 31st Air Division and the Air Technical Intelligence Center.
witnesses: caretaker at Shady Lanes Rest Home, 2LT Ivan Meiss of the 73rd ACU Squadron
